This select the way the controller outputs are setup!
in Line mode they are serial. So set the Nr of leds correctly and 
the correct starled for that output.
in Mirror mode all start al led 0 and do the same.
This is loaded at boot!

Type : Mode   : led_type  
0: Mirror :     MIX : Data1 + CLk 1 = APA102 ; Data3 = WS2812 ; Data4 = SK8622
5: Line	  :	    MIX : Data1 + CLk 1 = APA102 ; Data3 = WS2812 ; Data4 = SK8622

1: Line   :  APA102 : Data1+CLK & Data3+Data4(clk) = APA102
2: Mirror :  APA102 : Data1+CLK & Data3+Data4(clk) = APA102

3: Line   : WS2812b : Data1 to Data4 = WS2812b
4: Mirror : WS2812b : Data1 to Data4 = WS2812b

widgets.svg:
#{

# build the data array

data = [
  @{led_p1l00},
  @{led_p1l01},
  @{led_p1l02},
  @{led_p1l03},
  @{led_p1l04},
  @{led_p1l05},
  @{led_p1l06},
  @{led_p1l07},
  @{led_p1l08},
  @{led_p1l09},
  @{led_p1l10},
  @{led_p1l11},
  @{led_p1l12},
  @{led_p1l13},
  @{led_p1l14},
  @{led_p1l15},
  @{led_p1l00}
];

# extract channels and convert to relative y-axis coordinates
# assuming the range is 0-255

red = 100 - flatten(data[0:end,0]) / 255 * 100;
green = 100 - flatten(data[0:end,1]) / 255 * 100;
blue = 100 - flatten(data[0:end,2]) / 255 * 100;

# build the x-axis relative coordinates array

length = size(red)[0]
xaxis = (0:length) / (length-1) * 100;


# convert coords to svg path string
svgCoords(color) = map(color, f(c,i)=print("L$0%x $1%y", [xaxis[i], c]));

# svg path first command must be "M", not "L" 
svgString(color) = concat("M", unpack(svgCoords(color))[1:end]);

}


<path stroke="red" d="#{svgString(red)}" />
<path stroke="lime" d="#{svgString(green)}" />
<path stroke="blue" d="#{svgString(blue)}" />

There are 7 frequency bins.

the EQ chip will give a reading how oftern the frequency apperas since the last reading.

The Value above the Trigger will be put into the selected data line. 
Example: FFT RED+FFT-Bri selected. 
Trigger set to 100, Reading = 130, the falue of RED is +30 (130-100). 
The value of Britness = Master Britnes(50) + 30 = 80. 

FFT-BRI & FFT-FPS adds onto the configured Master-BRI / FPS. 
MAX-BRI is capped at 255, MAX-FPS is capped at 100
